"content": "<h2>Villages were small rural settlements without walls</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:31\">LEV 25:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:5\">DEU 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:16\">1CH 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:27-2Chr32:29\">2CH 32:27–32:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:19\">EST 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:11\">SNG 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:15\">MAT 14:15</a></p>\n<h2>Villages associated with neighbouring towns and cities</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:15\">JER 19:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:37\">JOS 10:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:23\">JOS 13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:18\">1SA 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:28\">NEH 12:28</a></p>\n<h2>Villages were particularly vulnerable to invasion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:11\">EZK 38:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:7\">JDG 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:14\">2CH 14:14</a></p>\n<h2>Village records and teachers</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:32\">1CH 4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:22\">1CH 9:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:17\">LUK 5:17</a></p>\n<h2>Villages as the scene of gospel preaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:6\">MRK 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:25\">ACT 8:25</a></p>",
